    <article id="text__paragraphs">
      <header>
        <h1>Paragraphs</h1>
      </header>
      <div>
        <div class="field">A paragraph (from the Greek paragraphos, “to write beside” or “written beside”) is a
          self-contained unit of a discourse in writing dealing with a particular point or idea. A paragraph consists of
          one or more sentences. Though not required
          by the syntax of any language, paragraphs are usually an expected part of formal writing, used to organize
          longer prose.</p>
        </div>
        <footer>
          <div class="field"><a href="#top">[Top]</a></p>
        </footer>
    </article>
    <article id="text__blockquotes">
