      <div>
        <blockquote>
          <div class="field">A block quotation (also known as a long quotation or extract) is a quotation in a written
            document, that is set off from the main text as a paragraph, or block of text.</p>
            <div class="field">It is typically distinguished visually using indentation and a different typeface or
              smaller size quotation. It may or may not include a citation, usually placed at the bottom.</p>
              <cite><a href="#!">Said no one, ever.</a></cite>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      <footer>
        <div class="field"><a href="#top">[Top]</a></p>
